race.comment: DIVINE SPARK (4) has powered home to just miss in both runs back and now finally draws a gate. Third-up and nearing her peak, with Richards sticking, she gets her chance to break through. EXTRA HANDS (9) is edging closer to a win and doesn't need to improve much to shed the maiden tag. Steps back out in trip and keeps the red-hot Boudvillain aboard. Major threat. MCTOMINAY (1) has been honest in all three runs this prep and should be cherry-ripe now. Heywood sticks from a favourable draw and he'll take plenty of running down. AQUILINO (7) was too bad to be true last start in town, but his prior form measures up strongly. With a smart steer from the wide alley, he can feature in the finish.
